03:28.368 --> 03:39.304
directly from the county. That's right. And 
usually the expenses, office, secretaries were

03:40.566 --> 03:52.583
furnished by the counties, and the agents were 
drawing anywhere from $20 to $30, $40, $50,

03:40.566 --> 03:52.583
depending on the situation, some of them much more 
than that, from the county. You'd get a separate

03:52.763 --> 03:53.785
check. You'd get a check from A&M and They took all 
the deductions out of here in terms of retirement

03:55.673 --> 04:01.360
programs and insurance and everything. And the 
county didn't do any of that. And so you had two

04:05.164 --> 04:10.050
checks that you got paid for. Anyway, after I had, 
and I worked in the administrative building over

04:10.731 --> 04:21.384
there because I had to have constant access to the 
administrative staff. And we often met with them

04:22.024 --> 04:24.347
to, you know, explore ideas and ways to do it, and 
then I'd have to do more number crunching, and they

04:24.817 --> 04:32.749
wanted this, and it didn't look right, so I'd do 
more number crunching. Anyway, I went through a

04:32.769 --> 04:45.167
lot of this, and then I also, during that period, 
was

04:32.769 --> 04:45.167
that afterwards? No, I guess that was later. 
