what was their working relationship and how do you 
think he felt about the extension service Rudder?

16:12.910 --> 16:14.452
Did they did they work well together? I think so I 
mean I think so Mr. Rudder had a good understanding

16:17.075 --> 16:28.487
of rural agricultural I mean he had that 
background himself I think he recognized the

16:17.075 --> 16:28.487
important role that the extension service played 
particularly in the 90 percent of the counties in

16:31.285 --> 16:57.965
of thing, and I think he recognized, which I always 
say, land grant, I have made the statement at land

16:31.285 --> 16:57.965
grant meetings that, you know, you get a lot of 
people that come out of non-land grant situations

16:31.285 --> 16:57.965
that get into leadership positions, and I always 
say that presidents of non-land grant

16:31.285 --> 16:57.965
universities would give their right arm to have 
what a land grant university president has with

16:31.285 --> 16:57.965
this outreach into every single community. I 
