because that's good history. Well, there was a 
period there when women started wearing what are

21:37.406 --> 21:44.237
called pantsuits, something like that, and he was 
just adamantly against it. He just thought it was

21:44.257 --> 21:48.403
not professionally appropriate, and I I guess I 
was a little of the younger generation, and I told

21:49.075 --> 21:54.403
him, don't waste your shots on it. It's a fashion 
thing. It's probably come and go. But he had a real

21:57.267 --> 22:00.532
hard time accepting it. You see, if you go back far 
enough in time, I mean, that generation, it was

22:00.973 --> 22:06.361
like school teaching. A woman couldn't teach if 
she was married, for example, or divorced or

22:06.641 --> 22:12.510
something like that. It was a different area. I 
think he had also... more conservative

22:16.278 --> 22:19.322
viewpoints about the racial thing. I mean, I'm 
sure that he felt the way the system had arranged

22:19.382 --> 22:31.317
it, and I think it was from a sincere basis that he 
felt the black community was better served with

22:19.382 --> 22:31.317
having their own professionals. They could 
relate to each other, and there's some evidence

22:31.998 --> 22:34.381
that's true. I mean, even now they try to identify 
people. There was one other thing I got very

22:39.187 --> 22:44.293
involved in that I'm very proud of that's, I guess, 
made my reputation a little more national is that I

22:44.594 --> 22:52.924
participated with the federal office. They had a 
small research unit at the Department of

22:52.964 --> 22:58.050
Agriculture in Washington, only a handful of 
people. But in the war and poverty time days, some

22:59.172 --> 23:05.940
monies became available for extra studies. We 
were very concerned that we, with our home

23:06.821 --> 23:12.087
economics program, particularly in nutrition, 
that we weren't you know, really reaching people

23:13.518 --> 23:17.305
effectively, the poorest of the poor. And this is 
very unusual for Extension to get involved that

23:18.507 --> 23:37.922
deeply, but there was a lady who was a research 
expert out of Washington, and if you look at my

